A N A C T
RELATING TO HEALTH AND SAFETY -- SEXUALLY TRANSMITTED DISEASES
Introduced By: Senators Murray, Valverde, Gu, Lawson, Sosnowski, Urso, and Vargas
Date Introduced: March 14, 2025
Referred To: Senate Health & Human Services
(Dept. of Health)
It is enacted by the General Assembly as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Section 23-11-8 of the General Laws in Chapter 23-11 entitled "Sexually
2 Transmitted Diseases" is hereby amended to read as follows:
3 23-11-8. Blood test of pregnant women.
4 It shall be the duty of every physician, midwife, physician assistant and nurse practitioner
5 engaged in prenatal attendance upon a pregnant woman to obtain a blood specimen of that pregnant
6 woman within thirty (30) days after the first professional visit and again obtain a blood specimen
7 during the third trimester. That blood specimen These blood specimens shall be submitted to the
8 laboratory of the state department of health, or to a laboratory approved by the department, for the
9 performance of a Wassermann or other standard laboratory blood test for syphilis. Any violation
10 of the provisions of this section shall constitute a misdemeanor and that physician, midwife,
11 physician assistant or nurse practitioner shall be fined not less than ten dollars ($10.00) nor more
12 than one hundred dollars ($100) for each offense.
13 SECTION 2. This act shall take effect upon passage.
